The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | England score 275 for four
                                                                                                                                                                                                     England score 275 for four
                      
	Leeds: Kevin Pietersen and Andrew Flintoff ran riot for England in the opening one-day International against South Africa on Friday, smashing a 158-run partnership in a total of 275 for four.         
	Pietersen hit an unbeaten 90 in just 82 balls while Flintoff scored a lusty 78 in just 70 deliveries before being bowled by Dale Steyn in the last over.         
